-Give it to me!
-Sign here.

785
00:56:25,424 --> 00:56:26,341
Hurry!

786
00:56:44,234 --> 00:56:45,527
Did you look into it?

787
00:56:46,904 --> 00:56:48,196
Yes, Mr. Kim.

788
00:56:48,280 --> 00:56:50,115
I asked a colleague in HR,

789
00:56:50,198 --> 00:56:52,534
and just like you said,
there was only one person.

790
00:56:52,618 --> 00:56:55,329
Someone who came back
to headquarters from the factory.

791
00:56:56,622 --> 00:56:58,999
It's Executive Director Sim Gang-hun.

792
00:56:59,082 --> 00:57:01,251
Back in 2008,
he went through the same thing you did.

793
00:57:01,335 --> 00:57:03,462
He was sent to the ACT
Tech Safety Management Team,

794
00:57:03,545 --> 00:57:06,965
then came back to headquarters
and even became an executive director.

795
00:57:11,762 --> 00:57:15,349
I practically begged and managed
to get his contact information.

796
00:57:15,432 --> 00:57:16,934
I'll text it to you.

797
00:57:18,018 --> 00:57:20,562
By the way,
how did you find out about this?

798
00:57:20,646 --> 00:57:23,482
LESS DOUBT, MORE DETERMINATION

799
00:57:42,209 --> 00:57:43,418
What?

800
00:57:52,010 --> 00:57:53,053
What's going on?

801
00:58:06,233 --> 00:58:08,068
Go around! No!

802
00:58:24,209 --> 00:58:25,085
DECEMBER 16, 2008

803
00:58:25,168 --> 00:58:26,753
After 182 days in this hell,

804
00:58:26,837 --> 00:58:31,091
I'm finally returning to headquarters.

805
00:58:31,925 --> 00:58:34,761
Don't you lose hope.

806
00:58:35,345 --> 00:58:38,056
It's your turn now.

807
00:58:44,396 --> 00:58:46,148
I'm not running for food.

808
00:58:47,315 --> 00:58:49,276
And it's not to beat this girl either.

809
00:58:50,152 --> 00:58:52,863
I'm running to prove
that this punishment was wrong.

810
00:58:52,946 --> 00:58:54,031
So that I, Kim Nak-su,

811
00:58:54,114 --> 00:58:56,700
can return as General Manager Kim
of ACT Group.

812
00:58:57,617 --> 00:59:00,662
That's why I'm running.

813
00:59:22,851 --> 00:59:23,852
Enjoy your meal.

814
00:59:27,189 --> 00:59:30,067
And you can wash the water bowl

815
00:59:30,150 --> 00:59:31,860
if you adore the dog that much.

816
00:59:35,906 --> 00:59:38,450
I'm going back. No matter what.

817
00:59:41,828 --> 00:59:48,794
THE DREAM LIFE OF MR. KIM

818
01:00:29,960 --> 01:00:32,087
You little… Come here!

819
01:01:28,351 --> 01:01:30,937
Let's bring Kim Nak-su back to HQ, sir.

820
01:01:31,938 --> 01:01:34,399
The only person
I can ask for help with this

821
01:01:35,317 --> 01:01:36,443
is you, sir.

822
01:01:37,611 --> 01:01:39,029
-Sung-gu!
-Mr. Kim!

823
01:01:39,112 --> 01:01:40,614
Still, you should treat him well.

824
01:01:40,697 --> 01:01:42,532
You might end up working for him again.

825
01:01:42,616 --> 01:01:45,493
Your humble subordinate, Kim Nak-su,
is here to greet you.

826
01:01:46,411 --> 01:01:49,456
You don't have anyone else
to count on in the Sales Team, anyway.

827
01:01:49,539 --> 01:01:50,999
Shouldn't you put in more effort

828
01:01:51,082 --> 01:01:53,460
at times like this to secure your career?

829
01:01:53,543 --> 01:01:56,254
The Asan factory
is the HR Team's biggest battle this year.

830
01:01:56,338 --> 01:01:57,380
Sir.

831
01:01:57,464 --> 01:01:59,591
We need your help.

832
01:02:00,342 --> 01:02:01,718
Ha-jin, I'm sorry.

833
01:02:02,302 --> 01:02:03,595
I really messed up.

834
01:02:03,678 --> 01:02:05,680
Subtitle translation by Yuri Kang
